{"key":"processedPost-12058725","value":{"id":12058725,"first":12055702,"last":12063769,"when":1266592621,"utime":"02/19/10 05:17 PM","content":"I'm currently inoculating well over 1000 lbs of rye berries per month, and do it all with grain to grain transfers.&nbsp; The main reason is if I inoculate 400 spawn bags with LC and it turns out bad, I've just lost 1500 pounds of pressure cooked grains.&nbsp; When doing g2g where one bag inoculates ten more, if one transfer goes bad, I only lose a maximum of ten bags.<br />Grains inoculated with other grains will take off faster than with LC.&nbsp; Where LC shines is in not waiting the ten days for a bag to colonize before using it for g2g.&nbsp; However, when doing a lot of bulk, the risk factor is too great with LC, thus I don't use it.<br />RR","title":"Re: Is G2G Obsolete?"}}